CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 27, 1969, pg. 7 reads:"Xmas In September - Christmas came early this year for Master David Southers, winner of the New Courier's second annual baby contest. Baby Southers, son of Mr. & Mrs. Carl Southers, of 756 Cherokee St., tallied over 365,000 votes to capture the title and a host of valuable prizes...Sitting majestically (center photo) atop the year's supply of Heinz Junior Baby Food he won, David examines a jar to see if it will open...-Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Dolores Southers and son David Southers seated on boxes of prize Heinz baby food products for the New Pittsburgh Courier's baby contest
